{"TopicId":151395,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"The James Webb Space Telescope and stuff","CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T09:21:34Z","PageNum":20,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-09T01:45:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224074900\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641692290\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsdfsaefresfsef\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224074900\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641692290\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere should be no way to mess that up with adjustable segments.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere could be 18 ways to mess that up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-01-09T01:46:20Z\u0022 title=\u002201/09/2022 01:46  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 9, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by JoeSchmuckatelli\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-09T01:59:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#101010;font-size:21.12px;\u0022\u003E\nThe first science images are expected in about six months.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#101010;font-size:21.12px;\u0022\u003E\n\u0022We start with the mirrors off by millimeters, and we\u0027re driving them to be aligned within less than the size of a coronavirus, like to tens of nanometers,\u0022 said Jane Rigby, Webb operations project scientist. \u0022It\u0027s this very deliberate process that is time consuming.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022border:none;color:#101010;font-size:0px;padding:0px;text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#101010;font-size:21.12px;\u0022\u003E\nRather than showing off initially blurry \u0022first light\u0022 images in the next few weeks, \u0022\u003Cstrong\u003Ewe want to make sure that the first images that the world sees ... do justice to this $10 billion telescope,\u0022 she said. \u0022So we are planning a series of \u0027wow\u0027 images to be released at the end of commissioning.\u003C/strong\u003E\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#101010;font-size:21.12px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.cbsnews.com/news/webb-space-telescope-nasa-deployments-successful/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EWebb telescope deployments complete as side mirrors rotate into place - CBS News\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-09T03:15:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224074905\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641693590\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na series of \u0027wow\u0027 images\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis exactly what I\u0027m hoping for.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need a new\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/8lZ8ujdxULU?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-09T05:14:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224074905\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641693590\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWebb telescope deployments complete as side mirrors rotate into place - CBS News\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022webb-labled.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.77\u0022 height=\u0022414\u0022 width=\u0022620\u0022 src=\u0022https://cbsnews3.cbsistatic.com/hub/i/r/2022/01/08/fc896b99-adfe-48b4-93b9-10c84431f664/thumbnail/620x414/617755927bcba73abd4a0b64b9e23b9d/webb-labled.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt the very left.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Momentum Flap\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlaps! They use flaps in vacuum! To manage the momentum!\u003Cbr\u003E\n(Even if this looks more like a fin, but anyway.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd the whole thing looks like a sailboat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAether exists!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224074930\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641698155\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/8lZ8ujdxULU?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022red-coloring-glass-water-red-food-colori\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.63\u0022 height=\u0022533\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022 src=\u0022https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/red-coloring-glass-water-red-food-coloring-glass-water-white-background-up-close-view-172133543.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd here again!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-01-09T05:18:43Z\u0022 title=\u002201/09/2022 05:18  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 9, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-09T05:38:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224074971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641705252\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAether exists\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy dear friends from the 1800s agree!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-09T15:57:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuestion - with the requirement of keeping the sun shield between the observatory and the sun, are there parts of the sky in the axis of the orbit that cannot be imaged?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Elthy","CreatedById":63317,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-09T16:12:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. The telescope can only image a \u0022ring\u0022 of the sky at a given moment, but as it circles around the sun that ring will hit every part of the sky within a year. Scott Manley has more details in his video about the JWST.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-09T18:58:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224075141\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641743831\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuestion - with the requirement of keeping the sun shield between the observatory and the sun, are there parts of the sky in the axis of the orbit that cannot be imaged?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt has about 60% of the sky available at any time. As it goes around the sun, it can see the full sky over time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-09T20:25:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224075202\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641754704\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt has about 60% of the sky available at any time. As it goes around the sun, it can see the full sky over time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah - I\u0027m getting that - but wondered if there was a region above or below the \u0027pole\u0027 of the orbit that it could not resolve b/c of the shade\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-09T21:00:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224075222\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641759951\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah - I\u0027m getting that - but wondered if there was a region above or below the \u0027pole\u0027 of the orbit that it could not resolve b/c of the shade\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is a direct link to Scott Manley\u0027s detailed explanation of all the orbits and angles (timestamp 6:23):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/cp_7AJseYYc?start=383\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-09T21:12:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224075226\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641762044\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScott Manley\u0027s detailed explanation of all the orbits and angles (timestamp 6:23\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks - that was great!\u00A0 Interestingly, he says that what actually happens is the exact \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Eopposite \u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003Eof what I feared: there are two small areas at the poles that are constantly viewable.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-10T05:26:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#000000;color:#aaaaaa;font-size:17.28px;\u0022\u003EAfter all individual mirror segment deployments are completed, the detailed optical mirror alignment process begins which is about a 3 month process. In parallel, as temperatures cool enough, instrument teams will turn on their instruments and begin each instrument\u0027s commissioning process.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://jwst.nasa.gov/content/observatory/ote/mirrors/index.html#8\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMirrors Webb/NASA\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tomf","CreatedById":57809,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-10T11:18:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will be like going to the opticians \u0022can you read the middle line of letters for me please. And is this better or worse, better or worse?\u0022 for 6 months solid.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-12T02:21:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nits like truing a bicycle rim.. every spoke you adjust affects the tension on all the other spokes.\u00A0takes forever. eventually you get to a point where its good enough to use.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-12T14:49:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Planetary_gear_Box.jpg_G%C4%B0F.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022110.67\u0022 height=\u0022332\u0022 width=\u0022300\u0022 src=\u0022https://monolib.s3.amazonaws.com/media/Planetary_gear_Box.jpg_G%C4%B0F.gif\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00221200px-One_wheel_motorcycle_Goventosa.jp\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002278.75\u0022 height=\u0022945\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/One_wheel_motorcycle_Goventosa.jpg/1200px-One_wheel_motorcycle_Goventosa.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo problem.\u003Cbr\u003E\nmousewheel rim \u002B several intracycles \u002B\u00A0 epicycling gearing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-14T17:48:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor those wanting more info, the current blog is a pretty good read:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://blogs.nasa.gov/webb/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EJames Webb Space Telescope (nasa.gov)\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#1a1a1a;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EEach mirror now needs to be deployed out by 12.5 millimeters (about half an inch) to get the pegs clear from the sockets. This will give the mirrors \u2018room to roam\u2019 and let them be readied in their starting positions for alignment.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#1a1a1a;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E...\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#1a1a1a;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003EAt full speed, it takes about a day to move all the segments by just 1 millimeter. It\u2019s about the same speed at which grass grows!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VaPaL","CreatedById":150974,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-14T19:23:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224077291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221642182493\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n12.5 millimeters\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not expected to be this much, I thought they would be much closer to final position... Maybe some small alignment due to rocket vibration or assembly tolerance, but only that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-14T19:28:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224077319\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221642188199\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150974\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VaPaL\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, VaPaL said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not expected to be this much, I thought they would be much closer to final position... Maybe some small alignment due to rocket vibration or assembly tolerance, but only that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApparently they wanted to make durned sure the mirrors were safe from vibrations (Abrupt clamp release, anyone?).\u00A0 Like you, I\u0027m surprised - but this certainly explains why they\u0027re spending so much time releasing and testing each mirror.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... Watching the grass grow?\u00A0 \u00A0Daaaaang.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VaPaL","CreatedById":150974,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-14T19:42:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224077322\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221642188521\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWatching the grass grow?\u00A0 \u00A0Daaaaang.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMirror position x time:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022green-graph-made-up-of-different-heights\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022459\u0022 width=\u0022612\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.istockphoto.com/photos/green-graph-made-up-of-different-heights-of-grass-picture-id183359226?s=612x612\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Elthy","CreatedById":63317,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-15T07:25:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anyone have technical details on those acctuators? How do they work, how are they so precise?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-15T16:31:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224077495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221642231510\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002263317\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Elthy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Elthy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anyone have technical details on those acctuators? How do they work, how are they so precise?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have no idea, but I would assume something similar to a worm-gear screw jack: slow but relatively torquey, allowing for great precision.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.33\u0022 height=\u0022542\u0022 style=\u0022width:600px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u0022964\u0022 alt=\u0022actuators-based-on-toothed-belt.jpg?anchor=center\u0026amp;mode=crop\u0026amp;width=964\u0026amp;height=542\u0026amp;upscale=false\u0026amp;quality=70\u0026amp;webpquality=50\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.bj-gear.com/media/1670/actuators-based-on-toothed-belt.jpg?anchor=center\u0026amp;mode=crop\u0026amp;width=964\u0026amp;height=542\u0026amp;upscale=false\u0026amp;quality=70\u0026amp;webpquality=50\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-15T19:12:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224077328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221642189341\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150974\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VaPaL\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, VaPaL said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMirror position x time:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI once described the movie 2001 as \u0022watching a glacier move\u0022, granted that was watching a VHS tape on a 1980s CRT TV.\u00A0 Watching the whole thing later on a real movie theater with Dolby sound was enjoyable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps NASA didn\u0027t include cameras partly to spare people the nagging feeling that they should be watching the JWST unfold.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-17T14:16:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224077637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221642264295\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/15/2022 at 5:31 PM, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have no idea, but I would assume something similar to a worm-gear screw jack: slow but relatively torquey, allowing for great precision.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.bj-gear.com/media/1670/actuators-based-on-toothed-belt.jpg?anchor=center\u0026amp;mode=crop\u0026amp;width=964\u0026amp;height=542\u0026amp;upscale=false\u0026amp;quality=70\u0026amp;webpquality=50\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022actuators-based-on-toothed-belt.jpg?anchor=center\u0026amp;mode=crop\u0026amp;width=964\u0026amp;height=542\u0026amp;upscale=false\u0026amp;quality=70\u0026amp;webpquality=50\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.33\u0022 height=\u0022542\u0022 style=\u0022width:600px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u0022964\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.bj-gear.com/media/1670/actuators-based-on-toothed-belt.jpg?anchor=center\u0026amp;mode=crop\u0026amp;width=964\u0026amp;height=542\u0026amp;upscale=false\u0026amp;quality=70\u0026amp;webpquality=50\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably now add an servo motor to it, might even have an gear box for more accuracy but making it even slower.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nPart of the reason why its slow is because its purpose is to bend the glass an fraction of an wavelength and you do not want this to break the mirror if one of them stops for an reason.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-17T14:56:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224078276\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221642428963\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n39 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably now add an servo motor to it, might even have an gear box for more accuracy but making it even slower.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nPart of the reason why its slow is because its purpose is to bend the glass an fraction of an wavelength and you do not want this to break the mirror if one of them stops for an reason.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe mirror is made of beryllium metal coated in gold, not glass. It won\u0027t break.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-01-17T14:57:00Z\u0022 title=\u002201/17/2022 02:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 17, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by cubinator\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VaPaL","CreatedById":150974,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-18T16:20:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1388723556\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://www.reddit.com/r/jameswebb/comments/s6yhct/all_mirrors_are_aligned_to_0mm_just_only_a3_and/\u0022 style=\u0022height:156px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022iuajvghhfgc81.png?width=1000\u0026amp;format=png\u0026amp;\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002294.80\u0022 height=\u0022948\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022 src=\u0022https://preview.redd.it/iuajvghhfgc81.png?width=1000\u0026amp;format=png\u0026amp;auto=webp\u0026amp;s=fb9ee7c9ac93113eaed8f8d1c5f57659308a60f2\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Not aligned... deployed*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-01-18T16:20:41Z\u0022 title=\u002201/18/2022 04:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 18, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by VaPaL\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}